{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1309,"text":"Seventy-thousand years ago, our ancestors\nwere insignificant animals."},{"time":6398,"text":"The most important thing to know\nabout prehistoric humans"},{"time":10521,"text":"is that they were unimportant."},{"time":12497,"text":"Their impact on the world was not\nmuch greater than that of jellyfish"},{"time":17655,"text":"or fireflies or woodpeckers."},{"time":20643,"text":"Today, in contrast,\nwe control this planet."},{"time":24853,"text":"And the question is:"},{"time":26219,"text":"How did we come from there to here?"},{"time":29666,"text":"How did we turn ourselves\nfrom insignificant apes,"},{"time":33342,"text":"minding their own business\nin a corner of Africa,"},{"time":36513,"text":"into the rulers of planet Earth?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39876,"text":"Usually, we look for the difference\nbetween us and all the other animals"},{"time":45590,"text":"on the individual level."},{"time":47412,"text":"We want to believe -- I want to believe --"},{"time":50430,"text":"that there is something special about me,"},{"time":54002,"text":"about my body, about my brain,"},{"time":57152,"text":"that makes me so superior\nto a dog or a pig, or a chimpanzee."},{"time":63221,"text":"But the truth is that,\non the individual level,"},{"time":66506,"text":"I'm embarrassingly similar\nto a chimpanzee."},{"time":70029,"text":"And if you take me and a chimpanzee\nand put us together on some lonely island,"},{"time":75288,"text":"and we had to struggle for survival\nto see who survives better,"},{"time":79560,"text":"I would definitely place my bet\non the chimpanzee, not on myself."},{"time":85419,"text":"And this is not something\nwrong with me personally."},{"time":88469,"text":"I guess if they took almost any one\nof you, and placed you alone"},{"time":92619,"text":"with a chimpanzee on some island,"},{"time":94608,"text":"the chimpanzee would do much better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98823,"text":"The real difference between humans\nand all other animals"},{"time":103032,"text":"is not on the individual level;"},{"time":105503,"text":"it's on the collective level."},{"time":107518,"text":"Humans control the planet\nbecause they are the only animals"},{"time":112348,"text":"that can cooperate both flexibly\nand in very large numbers."},{"time":118167,"text":"Now, there are other animals --"},{"time":119959,"text":"like the social insects,\nthe bees, the ants --"},{"time":123154,"text":"that can cooperate in large numbers,\nbut they don't do so flexibly."},{"time":128099,"text":"Their cooperation is very rigid."},{"time":131012,"text":"There is basically just one way\nin which a beehive can function."},{"time":135215,"text":"And if there's a new opportunity\nor a new danger,"},{"time":139050,"text":"the bees cannot reinvent\nthe social system overnight."},{"time":143617,"text":"They cannot, for example,\nexecute the queen"},{"time":146521,"text":"and establish a republic of bees,"},{"time":148451,"text":"or a communist dictatorship\nof worker bees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152442,"text":"Other animals, like the social mammals --"},{"time":154809,"text":"the wolves, the elephants,\nthe dolphins, the chimpanzees --"},{"time":158707,"text":"they can cooperate much more flexibly,"},{"time":161477,"text":"but they do so only in small numbers,"},{"time":164842,"text":"because cooperation among chimpanzees"},{"time":167739,"text":"is based on intimate knowledge,\none of the other."},{"time":171811,"text":"I'm a chimpanzee and you're a chimpanzee,"},{"time":174603,"text":"and I want to cooperate with you."},{"time":176430,"text":"I need to know you personally."},{"time":179049,"text":"What kind of chimpanzee are you?"},{"time":180843,"text":"Are you a nice chimpanzee?"},{"time":182280,"text":"Are you an evil chimpanzee?"},{"time":183957,"text":"Are you trustworthy?"},{"time":185425,"text":"If I don't know you, how can I\ncooperate with you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":189676,"text":"The only animal that can combine\nthe two abilities together"},{"time":193451,"text":"and cooperate both flexibly\nand still do so in very large numbers"},{"time":198771,"text":"is us, Homo sapiens."},{"time":200973,"text":"One versus one, or even 10 versus 10,"},{"time":205128,"text":"chimpanzees might be better than us."},{"time":208112,"text":"But, if you pit 1,000 humans\nagainst 1,000 chimpanzees,"},{"time":213315,"text":"the humans will win easily,\nfor the simple reason"},{"time":216957,"text":"that a thousand chimpanzees\ncannot cooperate at all."},{"time":221337,"text":"And if you now try to cram\n100,000 chimpanzees"},{"time":225412,"text":"into Oxford Street,\nor into Wembley Stadium,"},{"time":229052,"text":"or Tienanmen Square or the Vatican,"},{"time":231608,"text":"you will get chaos, complete chaos."},{"time":234249,"text":"Just imagine Wembley Stadium\nwith 100,000 chimpanzees."},{"time":238616,"text":"Complete madness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240219,"text":"In contrast, humans normally\ngather there in tens of thousands,"},{"time":246185,"text":"and what we get is not chaos, usually."},{"time":249273,"text":"What we get is extremely sophisticated\nand effective networks of cooperation."},{"time":256554,"text":"All the huge achievements\nof humankind throughout history,"},{"time":261168,"text":"whether it's building the pyramids\nor flying to the moon,"},{"time":264475,"text":"have been based not\non individual abilities,"},{"time":267074,"text":"but on this ability to cooperate\nflexibly in large numbers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271465,"text":"Think even about this very talk\nthat I'm giving now:"},{"time":275146,"text":"I'm standing here in front of an audience\nof about 300 or 400 people,"},{"time":281154,"text":"most of you are complete strangers to me."},{"time":284928,"text":"Similarly, I don't really know\nall the people who have organized"},{"time":289936,"text":"and worked on this event."},{"time":291994,"text":"I don't know the pilot\nand the crew members of the plane"},{"time":295811,"text":"that brought me over here,\nyesterday, to London."},{"time":299286,"text":"I don't know the people\nwho invented and manufactured"},{"time":303033,"text":"this microphone and these cameras,\nwhich are recording what I'm saying."},{"time":308123,"text":"I don't know the people\nwho wrote all the books and articles"},{"time":311684,"text":"that I read in preparation for this talk."},{"time":314495,"text":"And I certainly don't know all the people"},{"time":317329,"text":"who might be watching this talk\nover the Internet,"},{"time":320572,"text":"somewhere in Buenos Aires or in New Delhi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324162,"text":"Nevertheless, even though\nwe don't know each other,"},{"time":327695,"text":"we can work together to create\nthis global exchange of ideas."},{"time":334081,"text":"This is something chimpanzees cannot do."},{"time":337156,"text":"They communicate, of course,"},{"time":338994,"text":"but you will never catch a chimpanzee\ntraveling to some distant chimpanzee band"},{"time":344817,"text":"to give them a talk about bananas\nor about elephants,"},{"time":348961,"text":"or anything else that might\ninterest chimpanzees."},{"time":353389,"text":"Now cooperation is, of course,\nnot always nice;"},{"time":356903,"text":"all the horrible things humans\nhave been doing throughout history --"},{"time":360952,"text":"and we have been doing\nsome very horrible things --"},{"time":363715,"text":"all those things are also based\non large-scale cooperation."},{"time":368888,"text":"Prisons are a system of cooperation;"},{"time":371508,"text":"slaughterhouses are a system\nof cooperation;"},{"time":374522,"text":"concentration camps\nare a system of cooperation."},{"time":377907,"text":"Chimpanzees don't have slaughterhouses\nand prisons and concentration camps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384183,"text":"Now suppose I've managed\nto convince you perhaps that yes,"},{"time":388037,"text":"we control the world because we can\ncooperate flexibly in large numbers."},{"time":393516,"text":"The next question that immediately arises"},{"time":396488,"text":"in the mind of an inquisitive listener is:"},{"time":399395,"text":"How, exactly, do we do it?"},{"time":402083,"text":"What enables us alone, of all the animals,\nto cooperate in such a way?"},{"time":409714,"text":"The answer is our imagination."},{"time":412998,"text":"We can cooperate flexibly\nwith countless numbers of strangers,"},{"time":418454,"text":"because we alone, of all\nthe animals on the planet,"},{"time":422174,"text":"can create and believe fictions,\nfictional stories."},{"time":427326,"text":"And as long as everybody believes\nin the same fiction,"},{"time":431938,"text":"everybody obeys and follows\nthe same rules,"},{"time":435504,"text":"the same norms, the same values."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438639,"text":"All other animals use\ntheir communication system"},{"time":442562,"text":"only to describe reality."},{"time":445590,"text":"A chimpanzee may say, \"Look!\nThere's a lion, let's run away!\""},{"time":449831,"text":"Or, \"Look! There's a banana tree\nover there! Let's go and get bananas!\""},{"time":453961,"text":"Humans, in contrast, use their language\nnot merely to describe reality,"},{"time":460262,"text":"but also to create new realities,\nfictional realities."},{"time":465278,"text":"A human can say, \"Look,\nthere is a god above the clouds!"},{"time":469256,"text":"And if you don't do what I tell you to do,"},{"time":471360,"text":"when you die, God will punish you\nand send you to hell.\""},{"time":474986,"text":"And if you all believe this story\nthat I've invented,"},{"time":478782,"text":"then you will follow the same\nnorms and laws and values,"},{"time":482621,"text":"and you can cooperate."},{"time":484278,"text":"This is something only humans can do."},{"time":487207,"text":"You can never convince a chimpanzee\nto give you a banana"},{"time":491072,"text":"by promising him, \"... after you die,\nyou'll go to chimpanzee heaven ...\""},{"time":494889,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":495936,"text":"\"... and you'll receive lots and lots\nof bananas for your good deeds."},{"time":499222,"text":"So now give me this banana.\""},{"time":500668,"text":"No chimpanzee will ever\nbelieve such a story."},{"time":503776,"text":"Only humans believe such stories,"},{"time":506490,"text":"which is why we control the world,"},{"time":508597,"text":"whereas the chimpanzees are locked up\nin zoos and research laboratories."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514904,"text":"Now you may find it acceptable that yes,"},{"time":517868,"text":"in the religious field, humans cooperate\nby believing in the same fictions."},{"time":524032,"text":"Millions of people come together\nto build a cathedral or a mosque"},{"time":529008,"text":"or fight in a crusade or a jihad, because\nthey all believe in the same stories"},{"time":534774,"text":"about God and heaven and hell."},{"time":537979,"text":"But what I want to emphasize\nis that exactly the same mechanism"},{"time":543242,"text":"underlies all other forms\nof mass-scale human cooperation,"},{"time":549130,"text":"not only in the religious field."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551674,"text":"Take, for example, the legal field."},{"time":554531,"text":"Most legal systems today in the world\nare based on a belief in human rights."},{"time":561247,"text":"But what are human rights?"},{"time":563596,"text":"Human rights, just like God and heaven,\nare just a story that we've invented."},{"time":568322,"text":"They are not an objective reality;"},{"time":570664,"text":"they are not some biological effect\nabout homo sapiens."},{"time":574719,"text":"Take a human being,\ncut him open, look inside,"},{"time":578542,"text":"you will find the heart, the kidneys,\nneurons, hormones, DNA,"},{"time":583693,"text":"but you won't find any rights."},{"time":586200,"text":"The only place you find rights\nare in the stories"},{"time":590145,"text":"that we have invented and spread around\nover the last few centuries."},{"time":594607,"text":"They may be very positive stories,\nvery good stories,"},{"time":599561,"text":"but they're still just fictional stories\nthat we've invented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603664,"text":"The same is true of the political field."},{"time":606565,"text":"The most important factors\nin modern politics are states and nations."},{"time":613333,"text":"But what are states and nations?"},{"time":615593,"text":"They are not an objective reality."},{"time":617742,"text":"A mountain is an objective reality."},{"time":620479,"text":"You can see it, you can touch it,\nyou can even smell it."},{"time":624223,"text":"But a nation or a state,"},{"time":626019,"text":"like Israel or Iran or France or Germany,"},{"time":629823,"text":"this is just a story that we've invented"},{"time":632587,"text":"and became extremely attached to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634949,"text":"The same is true of the economic field."},{"time":637892,"text":"The most important actors today\nin the global economy"},{"time":641622,"text":"are companies and corporations."},{"time":644407,"text":"Many of you today, perhaps, work\nfor a corporation,"},{"time":648162,"text":"like Google or Toyota or McDonald's."},{"time":651577,"text":"What exactly are these things?"},{"time":653982,"text":"They are what lawyers call legal fictions."},{"time":658359,"text":"They are stories invented and maintained"},{"time":661859,"text":"by the powerful wizards we call lawyers."},{"time":665216,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":666685,"text":"And what do corporations do all day?"},{"time":670128,"text":"Mostly, they try to make money."},{"time":673411,"text":"Yet, what is money?"},{"time":674768,"text":"Again, money is not an objective reality;\nit has no objective value."},{"time":679958,"text":"Take this green piece\nof paper, the dollar bill."},{"time":683299,"text":"Look at it -- it has no value."},{"time":685700,"text":"You cannot eat it, you cannot drink it,"},{"time":687958,"text":"you cannot wear it."},{"time":689633,"text":"But then came along\nthese master storytellers --"},{"time":693698,"text":"the big bankers,"},{"time":695206,"text":"the finance ministers,"},{"time":696670,"text":"the prime ministers --"},{"time":698048,"text":"and they tell us a very convincing story:"},{"time":700550,"text":"\"Look, you see this green piece of paper?"},{"time":702532,"text":"It is actually worth 10 bananas.\""},{"time":705591,"text":"And if I believe it, and you believe it,"},{"time":707724,"text":"and everybody believes it,"},{"time":709264,"text":"it actually works."},{"time":711152,"text":"I can take this worthless piece of paper,"},{"time":714089,"text":"go to the supermarket,"},{"time":715750,"text":"give it to a complete stranger\nwhom I've never met before,"},{"time":719781,"text":"and get, in exchange, real bananas\nwhich I can actually eat."},{"time":724870,"text":"This is something amazing."},{"time":726615,"text":"You could never do it with chimpanzees."},{"time":728717,"text":"Chimpanzees trade, of course:"},{"time":730686,"text":"\"Yes, you give me a coconut,\nI'll give you a banana.\""},{"time":733460,"text":"That can work."},{"time":734722,"text":"But, you give me\na worthless piece of paper"},{"time":737738,"text":"and you except me to give you a banana?"},{"time":739776,"text":"No way!"},{"time":740952,"text":"What do you think I am, a human?"},{"time":742557,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":744954,"text":"Money, in fact, is\nthe most successful story"},{"time":749097,"text":"ever invented and told by humans,"},{"time":751777,"text":"because it is the only story\neverybody believes."},{"time":756692,"text":"Not everybody believes in God,"},{"time":759506,"text":"not everybody believes in human rights,"},{"time":762555,"text":"not everybody believes in nationalism,"},{"time":765364,"text":"but everybody believes in money,\nand in the dollar bill."},{"time":769514,"text":"Take, even, Osama Bin Laden."},{"time":771519,"text":"He hated American politics\nand American religion"},{"time":775230,"text":"and American culture,"},{"time":776703,"text":"but he had no objection\nto American dollars."},{"time":779533,"text":"He was quite fond of them, actually."},{"time":781652,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":784166,"text":"To conclude, then:"},{"time":785890,"text":"We humans control the world\nbecause we live in a dual reality."},{"time":792531,"text":"All other animals live\nin an objective reality."},{"time":796992,"text":"Their reality consists\nof objective entities,"},{"time":801568,"text":"like rivers and trees\nand lions and elephants."},{"time":806067,"text":"We humans, we also live\nin an objective reality."},{"time":809774,"text":"In our world, too, there are rivers\nand trees and lions and elephants."},{"time":815421,"text":"But over the centuries,"},{"time":817290,"text":"we have constructed on top\nof this objective reality"},{"time":822041,"text":"a second layer of fictional reality,"},{"time":825558,"text":"a reality made of fictional entities,"},{"time":829146,"text":"like nations, like gods,\nlike money, like corporations."},{"time":834481,"text":"And what is amazing is that\nas history unfolded,"},{"time":839139,"text":"this fictional reality became\nmore and more powerful"},{"time":844559,"text":"so that today, the most powerful\nforces in the world"},{"time":849084,"text":"are these fictional entities."},{"time":851715,"text":"Today, the very survival of rivers\nand trees and lions and elephants"},{"time":858533,"text":"depends on the decisions and wishes\nof fictional entities,"},{"time":863662,"text":"like the United States, like Google,\nlike the World Bank --"},{"time":868223,"text":"entities that exist only\nin our own imagination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872929,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":874105,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":884299,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Yuval, you have\na new book out."},{"time":886533,"text":"After Sapiens, you wrote another one,"},{"time":888360,"text":"and it's out in Hebrew, but not\nyet translated into ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":890971,"text":"Yuval Noah Harari: I'm working on\nthe translation as we speak."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893924,"text":"BG: In the book, if I\nunderstand it correctly,"},{"time":896116,"text":"you argue that the amazing breakthroughs\nthat we are experiencing right now"},{"time":901769,"text":"not only will potentially\nmake our lives better,"},{"time":904052,"text":"but they will create -- and I quote you --"},{"time":906312,"text":"\"... new classes and new class struggles,\njust as the industrial revolution did.\""},{"time":910954,"text":"Can you elaborate for us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":912670,"text":"YNH: Yes. In the industrial revolution,"},{"time":914618,"text":"we saw the creation of a new class\nof the urban proletariat."},{"time":919544,"text":"And much of the political and social\nhistory of the last 200 years involved"},{"time":924678,"text":"what to do with this class,\nand the new problems and opportunities."},{"time":928328,"text":"Now, we see the creation of a new\nmassive class of useless people."},{"time":932984,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":934009,"text":"As computers become better and better\nin more and more fields,"},{"time":939394,"text":"there is a distinct possibility that\ncomputers will out-perform us"},{"time":944310,"text":"in most tasks and will make\nhumans redundant."},{"time":947937,"text":"And then the big political\nand economic question"},{"time":950698,"text":"of the 21st century will be,"},{"time":953085,"text":"\"What do we need humans for?\","},{"time":955271,"text":"or at least, \"What do we need\nso many humans for?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":958662,"text":"BG: Do you have an answer in the book?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":961144,"text":"YNH: At present, the best guess\nwe have is to keep them happy"},{"time":965188,"text":"with drugs and computer games ..."},{"time":967009,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":968034,"text":"but this doesn't sound\nlike a very appealing future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971329,"text":"BG: Ok, so you're basically saying\nin the book and now,"},{"time":974162,"text":"that for all the discussion\nabout the growing evidence"},{"time":976972,"text":"of significant economic inequality,\nwe are just kind of at the beginning"},{"time":980759,"text":"of the process?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":982225,"text":"YNH: Again, it's not a prophecy;"},{"time":983775,"text":"it's seeing all kinds\nof possibilities before us."},{"time":987742,"text":"One possibility is this creation\nof a new massive class of useless people."},{"time":992748,"text":"Another possibility is\nthe division of humankind"},{"time":995912,"text":"into different biological castes,"},{"time":998927,"text":"with the rich being upgraded\ninto virtual gods,"},{"time":1003242,"text":"and the poor being degraded\nto this level of useless people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007574,"text":"BG: I feel there is another TED talk\ncoming up in a year or two."},{"time":1010620,"text":"Thank you, Yuval, for making the trip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012466,"text":"YNH: Thanks!"},{"time":1013646,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}